    <text>
        <front>
            <div type="abstract">
                <p tid="1">Short sūtra or tantra texts used mainly for ritual purposes, mostly structured around an incantation in Sanskrit, its uses and the story of its origin (Toh 846-1108).</p>
            </div>
        </front>
        <body>
            <div type="about">
                <head type="about" tid="3">Incantations</head>
                <div type="section" xml:id="EFT-KB-Dhāraṇīs-KANGYUR-SECTION-about-1">
                    <milestone unit="chunk" xml:id="O1JC114941JC14717-1"/>
                    <p tid="2">This broad section of Incantations, which corresponds to the <title xml:lang="Bo-Ltn">gzungs ’dus</title> division of the Degé Kangyur, contains two subdivisions: the
                        Compendium of Incantations, a collection of 249 <foreign type="term" xml:lang="Sa-Ltn">dhāraṇī</foreign> incantations themselves (Toh 846-1093), and a small group of 15 texts
                        (Toh 1094-1108) included at the end of the section as a whole by way of dedication and aspiration prayers.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </body>
